[SPEAKER_03]: I think there's a little bit of a pause here.

113
00:10:44,453 --> 00:11:05,670
[SPEAKER_03]: It wouldn't be a bad thing just to see if there's an opportunity because it's going to cost many hundreds of thousands of dollars to take this all down and build a brand new two-family, which presumably is larger, but I'm just trying to imagine how much larger it could be given the amount of square footage on this site between the three structures.

114
00:11:10,441 --> 00:11:11,562
[SPEAKER_12]: Great.

115
00:11:11,622 --> 00:11:17,548
[SPEAKER_12]: Having heard from all the commissioners, any comment from the homeowner or applicant?

116
00:11:22,112 --> 00:11:23,994
[SPEAKER_00]: Do you want to know why I want to do this?

117
00:11:24,374 --> 00:11:24,734
[SPEAKER_13]: Sure.

118
00:11:25,235 --> 00:11:28,318
[SPEAKER_13]: Denise, if you would just name for the record and the address, please.

119
00:11:28,378 --> 00:11:31,241
[SPEAKER_00]: Denise Rogier, 69 Court Street.

120
00:11:31,261 --> 00:11:35,545
[SPEAKER_12]: All right, floor is yours.

121
00:11:38,543 --> 00:11:43,645
[SPEAKER_01]: This has been something that I've been looking at for the past couple of years.

122
00:11:44,265 --> 00:11:51,048
[SPEAKER_01]: So my plans from two years ago to what they are now are a little bit smaller.

123
00:11:52,388 --> 00:11:57,010
[SPEAKER_01]: What I'm trying to do is I'm trying to stay in the house.

124
00:11:57,390 --> 00:12:00,551
[SPEAKER_01]: When we first put the addition on the back, back in the 80s,

125
00:12:03,559 --> 00:12:06,301
[SPEAKER_01]: My family was young and everything like that.

126
00:12:06,862 --> 00:12:10,645
[SPEAKER_01]: What happened is over the years, my husband ended up with cancer.

127
00:12:10,825 --> 00:12:19,153
[SPEAKER_01]: And so for the 20 years that we lived here before he passed away, we ended up more or less on one floor.

128
00:12:20,214 --> 00:12:25,679
[SPEAKER_01]: So after that happened, my father came and stayed with me for a while.

129
00:12:26,299 --> 00:12:26,579
[SPEAKER_01]: Again,

130
00:12:27,939 --> 00:12:33,682
[SPEAKER_01]: using the first floor for everything, which means using the living room as a bedroom.

131
00:12:35,263 --> 00:12:43,648
[SPEAKER_01]: So what I'm trying to do is I'm trying to change the house around so I can have everything on one floor front to back.

132
00:12:44,308 --> 00:12:47,190
[SPEAKER_01]: So as I get older, I can stay here.

133
00:12:49,091 --> 00:12:55,935
[SPEAKER_13]: So just to summarize for Doug, clean slate that allows an easier age in place rebuild.

134
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:58,408
[SPEAKER_01]: That's that's it.

135
00:12:58,748 --> 00:13:01,310
[SPEAKER_13]: Yeah, I think that's I think that's an appropriate summary.

136
00:13:01,831 --> 00:13:02,071
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah.

137
00:13:03,132 --> 00:13:11,139
[SPEAKER_01]: So, but I do understand what you're looking at is the back of the house the addition we put on is pretty interesting, but did some.

138
00:13:13,082 --> 00:13:14,643
[SPEAKER_01]: It's not working.

139
00:13:14,703 --> 00:13:23,965
[SPEAKER_01]: Talking to a couple of construction people, they said it would be easier to rip everything down and go from there and just rebuild the whole thing.

140
00:13:25,005 --> 00:13:31,106
[SPEAKER_01]: Of course, going back two years ago, things were a little bit different and I'm having a little bit of a different view now.

141
00:13:31,966 --> 00:13:39,688
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm trying to think of some way of taking the front of the house off, the old part, and maybe work it in to the back of the house.

142
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:45,621
[SPEAKER_12]: Does that answer your question?

143
00:13:47,622 --> 00:13:47,982
[SPEAKER_03]: It does.

144
00:13:48,282 --> 00:13:49,623
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you very much for the explanation.

145
00:13:50,103 --> 00:13:59,068
[SPEAKER_03]: I think that's what I would say is that's the point of this process is to pause and say, is there a different way to do it that gets you what you need?

146
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:01,189
[SPEAKER_03]: We want to get you what you need to function in that house.

147
00:14:01,229 --> 00:14:06,852
[SPEAKER_03]: That is absolutely 100 percent in favor of what you're trying to do here.

148
00:14:06,872 --> 00:14:07,892
[SPEAKER_03]: I think it's fantastic.

149
00:14:09,253 --> 00:14:11,414
[SPEAKER_03]: It sounds like do you want to

150
00:14:13,446 --> 00:14:30,155
[SPEAKER_03]: think about it or do a little bit more planning so that maybe you could come back with a plan that oddly enough keeps the house that's from the 80s and redesigns or maybe makes a second floor of the front house that could give you what you need without having to start over with a clean slate?

151
00:14:30,355 --> 00:14:31,476
[SPEAKER_03]: Is that a possibility?

152
00:14:34,057 --> 00:14:36,979
[SPEAKER_01]: Are you asking if I could come back with better plans?

153
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:41,343
[SPEAKER_03]: Well, it sounds like your plans have changed, right?

154
00:14:41,403 --> 00:14:42,725
[SPEAKER_03]: And yes, a complete demolition.

155
00:14:42,745 --> 00:14:43,707
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes, they have.

156
00:14:44,348 --> 00:14:47,673
[SPEAKER_01]: The plans I've already submitted down to City Hall.

157
00:14:50,120 --> 00:15:00,243
[SPEAKER_01]: They're tearing the whole house down and actually putting a garage in the front of the house because that's one of the things I want is a garage.

158
00:15:01,784 --> 00:15:12,147
[SPEAKER_01]: I was trying to make it so I would still have some space in the back to use as yard without putting the garage back there.

159
00:15:13,944 --> 00:15:19,109
[SPEAKER_01]: But we've been talking, I've been talking to the architect a little bit and seeing if we can change things around.

160
00:15:19,809 --> 00:15:23,533
[SPEAKER_01]: So if you think it would be best if I come back with something a little bit different.

161
00:15:25,890 --> 00:15:32,452
